The area

Address
Neighborhood: Louvre / Palais-Royal
From the majestic Louvre to the regal Palais-Royal, this neighborhood oozes luxury. The grand arches along Rue de Rivoli are shadowed by mosaics in front of decorated vitrines and hotels. Place Vendôme is lined with the world’s best jewelers and their glittering window displays. Every other establishment has someone to open the door for you or park your car. You can spend hours gazing at its haute couture shops or lingering over a meal at any of its chic eateries. After all that indulgence, the Tuileries gardens provide stately respite, while theaters compete for your applause. It's a neighborhood that draws admirers from around the world, all attracted to the luxe life in Paris.
How to get there
  • Tuileries • 3 min walk
  • Musée d'Orsay • 4 min walk

    Beautiful well kept gardens
    What a nice garden! The grounds are huge. It connects the Musee de l'Orangerie and the Louvre. After we saw the line for Musee de l'Orangerie was way too long, we decided to ditch those plans and stroll through the garden instead. It was around 11 am on a Wednesday and there were so many people sitting by the fountains. Made me wonder if they had work or not, or if French people just know how to enjoy life. There was also some kind of summer carnival going on at the time (mid-August) complete with food vendors, and some pretty impressive temporary amusement park rides. The grounds are well kept and the park is clean. I could definitely see me having some picnics here if I was a local. Overall, great spot for a break from city life and enjoy some fresh air.

Charming city park and garden in the Right Bank
Sep 2024 • Couples
This is an elegant Parisian garden situated between Place de la Concorde (northwest) and Place du Carrousel (southeast) on the Right Bank of Paris. Formerly the grounds of the Tuileries Palace, the garden was opened to the public in 1667 and became an official city park following the French Revolution.

For centuries it has been a place for Parisians and tourists alike to stroll through garden grounds, enjoying basins, groves of trees, walking paths and a wide range of monuments scattered throughout. There are metal chairs and benches to rest and relax within the gardens, a handful of cafes as well as important art museums including L'Orangerie, d'Orsay and the Louvre at or just beyond the Tuileries Gardens.

Well worth making time to spend strolling the garden grounds during visits to Paris. It is a nice place year round and conveniently located making it fairly easy to add to sightseeing plans while spending time in the city.
Written November 12, 2024

Ryan Otto Ulrich

Aux Tuileries
Jul 2024 • Friends
As is true with many central gathering points in Paris, here you'll find a microcosm of locals and visitors of all stripes. Travelers on a purposeful stroll, buskers, peddlers, cops, and locals all stream through the same ever-changing yet constant space that is the Jardin des Tuileries. It's brilliant for people-watching, dog-watching, reading, strolling and just staring off into space. Come here enough times, as I have, and you start to zoom in on different parts of it each time. Even in the madhouse that is Paris leading up to the Games of the XXXIII Olympiad, the Tuileries provide a splendid stage for life to unfold.
Written July 20, 2024

pro con advice- my experience of these gardens
Mar 2024 • Solo
PROS
* Famous historical park connecting famous historical places and museums
* Green areas for rest and relaxation
* Numerous statues commemorating and honoring famous ancient people

CONS
* Not much excitement other than to walk through it

"I VISITED THIS PLACE"...
... as an essential part of my plan to visit and write about absolutely everything that I could during my visit to Paris.

Practically speaking, I used it to traverse between my visit to the Louvre Museum and my visit to the Musee de l'Orangerie.

It was OK.

WAS IT WORTH THE COST?
It is free

WOULD "I VISIT THIS PLACE" AGAIN?
Yes, for transfer between world class museums

ADVICE
Go and enjoy- there is even a restaurant
